instance dt_constellation : DTDFVocab:Constellation [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin system follows the Digital Shadow Reference Model (DSRM) as defined by Kritzinger et al. It consists of three layers: the Asset layer representing the physical robot axis, the Model layer containing a SysML-based model and a UML class diagram (Fig. 1) that defines the conceptual relationships, and the Processing layer that performs contextual data aggregation and abstraction. The architecture is expressed through SysML IBDs and UML class diagrams, enabling integration of functional and logical descriptions in a single model."
]

instance fidelity_and_validity_considerations : DTDFVocab:FidelityConsideration [
    base:desc "Model validity is ensured by continuous comparison between Simulink simulation outputs and the live encoder measurements collected on the twin. Any statistically significant divergence over successive samples is flagged for investigation, and the twin logs the discrepancy. Data integrity checks on the MQTT stream include packet sequence verification to detect loss or reordering. Periodic re‑initialization of the simulation state aligns the model with the measured system, mitigating drift over long runs."
]
